1 (f) For students with a level 6 disability, multiplying $11,838.15 by the number
2 of students reported to have a level 6 disability on the child count for the
3 previous school fiscal year; and
4 (g) Adding together the products of subsections (a) to (f), inclusive.
5 (14) "Nonpublic fall enrollment," the sum of the number of children under age eighteen,
6 who are approved for alternative instruction, pursuant to § 13-27-3, on the last
7 Friday of September of the previous school year and:
8 (a) For a nonpublic school located within the boundaries of a school district that
