10 students in any grade from kindergarten through twelve, enrolled on the
11 last Friday of September of the previous regular school year in all nonpublic
12 schools located within the boundaries of the school district; or
13 (b) For a nonpublic school located within the boundaries of a school district that
14 had a fall enrollment of fewer than six hundred students, the number of
15 resident students in any grade from kindergarten through twelve, enrolled
16 on the last Friday of September of the previous school year in all nonpublic
17 schools located within this state;
18 (15) "Nonpublic school," a sectarian organization or entity accredited by the secretary
19 of the Department of Education for the purpose of instructing children of
20 compulsory school age, provided that the organization or entity does not receive a
21 majority of its revenues from public funds;
22 (16) "Nonresident student," any student who is in the care and custody of a state agency
23 and attends a public school outside of the school district in which the student is a
24 resident;
25 (17) "Special education fall enrollment," the enrollment number used to calculate
26 funding for students with a level one disability, as determined by adding the
