1098A 7 1098
1 (c) The amount set aside for the South Dakota School for the Blind and Visually
2 Impaired.
3 Beginning July 1, 2026, and every year thereafter, the amount of money allocated
4 to provide special education or special education and related services to each student in
5 each level of disability, pursuant to subsections (13)(a) to (13)(f), inclusive, must be
6 increased by the index factor.
7 Section 3. That § 13-37-55 be AMENDED:
8 13-37-55. Up to fifteen percent of the local need as defined in subdivision 13-37-
9 35.1(18) § 13-37-35.1 may be used to develop and implement coordinated, early
10 intervening services for students in kindergarten through grade twelve who are not
11 currently identified as needing special education or special education and related services,
12 but who need additional academic and behavioral interventions to succeed in a general
13 education environment to prevent them from being identified as having a special education
14 disability.
15 Coordinated, early intervening services include:
16 (1) Professional development for teachers and other school staff to enable them to
17 deliver scientifically-based academic instruction and behavioral interventions,
18 including scientifically-based literacy instruction, and, if appropriate, instruction on
19 the use of adaptive and instructional software; and
20 (2) Providing educational and behavioral evaluations, services and supports, including
21 scientifically-based literacy instruction.
